import json
from flask import Flask, jsonify

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def hello():
    return jsonify({"message": "Hello, I'm a serverless Flask app on Lambda!"})

# AWS Lambda handler
def lambda_handler(event, context):
    return app.full_dispatch_request()

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run()

This snippet demonstrates a basic Flask application wrapped for AWS Lambda. It leverages the serverless architecture to avoid idle costs and scales automatically with traffic.
